############################################################################

@NODE INTRO "Introduction"

  MUIBank is a banking account manager, simple and clean, using MUI.

There are already numerous programms of this sort available, but none
that would satisfy me, because they all have their flaws:  some are
poorly programmed with regard to the system, others are incomprehensive
(even those that claim that they are user-friendly!), and of course
none of them uses MUI which I find to be a "must" for the modern Amiga!

  MUIBank is simple, efficent and gives options for setting parameters.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE CONFIG "Configuration"

  MUIBank was developed on an Amiga 1200 with MUI 3.8. Generally, the
characteristics of your machine should be the following:

@{b}System      :@{ub} 2.1 and newer versions.
@{b}MUI         :@{ub} 3.3 and newer versions.
              (The latest version of MUI is recommended!).
@{b}Processor   :@{ub} 68000 and up.
@{b}FPU         :@{ub} useless.
@{b}Memory      :@{ub} Enough to load MUI, and a little more for MUIBank.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE INSTALL "Installation"

  The installation of MUIBank is absolutely simple!

@{b}Automatic installation:@{ub}
A manual on how to install the program is provided with MUIBank for your
convenience. Double-click on the installation icon and follow the
instructions.

@{b}Uninstall:@{ub}
If you are not satisfied with the software (oh well?!), you can uninstall
it by deleting the MUIBank files.

@{b}Note:@{ub}
Without the slightest exception, all the necessary files for MUIBank are
installed within the MUIBank directory. If all software were installed in
that manner, the hard drives would operate much cleaner!

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE EMPLOI "Manual"

This manual was not supposed to appear didactic, but it will provide
important information about graphic objects that the user will encounter.

    @{"      Main Window      " LINK PRINCIP}  The first window displayed.
    @{"    Details Window     " LINK DETAILS}  Edit a transaction.
    @{"    Display Window     " LINK AFFICHAGE}  Display options.
    @{"       Printer         " LINK IMPRESSION}  Printing parameters.
    @{"     Lists Window      " LINK LISTES}  Type and Characteristics dialog boxes.
    @{" Automatic Transaction " LINK OPAUTO}  Automatic operations.
    @{"     Query Window      " LINK REQ}  Create queries.
    @{"        Menus          " LINK MENUS}  The different menu options.
    @{"      ToolTypes        " LINK TOOLTYPES}  The ToolTypes available.


Note: MUIBank provides @{b}on-line help@{ub}. Do not hesitate to click the help
button in MUIBank. If you leave the mouse pointer on certain objects for a
certain time, a pop-up box will appear giving  you specific information.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE PRINCIP "Main Window"

The main window is basically composed of a list which displays all the
possible operations. One can also see the debit, the credit and the total
balance. This window also allows to add, modify or delete transactions.

@{b}Debit:@{ub} This button opens the @{" Details Window " LINK DETAILS} to add a debit
transaction.

@{b}Credit:@{ub} This button opens the @{" Details Window " LINK DETAILS} to add a credit
transaction.

@{b}Details:@{ub} This button opens the @{" Details Window" LINK DETAILS} in order to modify
the selected transaction in the list.

@{b}Delete:@{ub} This button deletes the selected transaction from the list.

@{b}Query:@{ub} This button allows to choose the query to activate. Only
transactions selected by the criteria of the query are displayed. If you
choose "None", every transaction is displayed because no query is
activated.
To create queries, please refer to @{" Query Window " LINK REQ}.

@{b}Type of balance:@{ub} This object allows to select which type of balance
should be displayed. An explanation of the different types of balance
follows.

    @{b}Banking:@{ub} This balance only takes those transactions into account
    that don't have "*", i.e. only the transactions that occured by
    reopening the account.
    The transactions without "*" indicating a date of the transaction
    ulterior to those of the system, if those are also not taken by
    the account.
    @{b}Real:@{ub} This balance takes transactions into account that don't
    have a date subsequent to those of the Amiga system.
    @{b}Theoretical:@{ub} This balance takes all transactions into account.

@{b}List:@{ub} The list displays all the transactions of the account.
If you double-click the column "*", the "*" dialog box changes.
A transaction with an empty  "*" dialog box has to have an operation date.
If this is not the case, MUIBank will apply the system date.

@{b}Filter:@{ub} The filter allows to display the transactions which correspond
to a specified criterion. MUIBank filters in accordance with the date of
the transmission. If the filter is typed by hand, it must be accepted by pushing
enter.
   _ @{b}No filter:@{ub} If the topic string is empty, all the transactions
     are visible.
   _ @{b}Monthly filter:@{ub} If the topic string contains a date, e.g.
     MM.YYYY, then only the transactions of the month MM in the year
     YYYY are displayed.
   _ @{b} Year filter:@{ub} If the topic string contains a date like
     YYYY, only the transaction of the year YYYY will be displayed.
   _ @{b}*:@{ub} This button deletes the filter.
   _ @{b}- and +:@{ub} With these two buttons you can change the filter value.
     @{b}PS:@{ub} If there is no existing filter, MUIBank will apply
     a month filter of the current month.
     If the topic string contains a month filter, the filter will
     be increased or decreased by a month.
     If the filter is a year filter, the value will be increased
     or decreased by a year.
   _ @{b}<:@{ub} Displays all the previous transactions in the filter.
   _ @{b}>:@{ub} Displays all the posterior transactions in the filter.
     @{b}PS:@{ub} If there is no existing filter, the month filter
     will be applied.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE DETAILS "Details Window"

  In the details window you can edit or create a transaction. The different
dialog boxes of a transaction are displayed and, of course, can be modified.
The following is a description of the dialog boxes.

@{b}Debit/Credit:@{ub} This "cycle" allows you to choose wheather it is a credit
or debit transaction.

@{b}Transmission:@{ub} This dialog box indicates the date when the transaction
was transmitted. The date has to be valid and it has to have the format
"DD.MM.YY".

@{b}Transaction:@{ub} This dialog box indicates the date when the transaction
actually has or should take place. This section may stay empty; if this is
not the case, the date cannot be anterior to that of the transmission.

@{b}Number:@{ub}This dialog box indicates the number of the transaction.
This section is optional.

@{b}Amount:@{ub}This dialog box indicates the amount of the transaction.

@{b}Type:@{ub} This cycle allows you to select the type of transaction (e.g.: check).
The values can be edited in the @{" lists window" LINK LISTES}.

@{b}Characteristics:@{ub} This cycle allows you to select the characteristics
of the transaction (e.g.:food).
The values can be edited in the @{" lists window " LINK LISTES}.

@{b}Commentary:@{ub} This dialog box gives more information about the transaction.
Its content is your choice.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE AFFICHAGE "Display Window"

  The display window allows you to set a parameter for the visualization
of the transactions in the main window.

@{b}Available dialog boxes:@{ub} This list allows you to sort the dialog boxes
with "Drag and Drop" according to their display order in the main list.
The dialog boxes appearing under "---------------" will not be displayed.
Select an element, keep the mouse button pushed, move the mouse (toward
the top or bottom) and let go of the mouse button: you now have changed
the order of the dialog box display.

@{b}Default query:@{ub} This object allows to choose the query to activate
when loading the account. Suggested queries are those that you created.

@{b}Balance by default:@{ub} By modifying the value of this object you choose
a type of balance which will be displayed when charging the account.

@{b}Filter by default:@{ub} This object allows to choose the type of filter
type which should be displayed when charging the account.
  None    : No transaction is filtered.
  Monthly : Only the transactions of the current month are being
            displayed.
  Annual  : Only the transactions of the current year are being
            displayed.

@{b}Total by default:@{ub} This object allows you to select the type of
totals which will be displayed when charging the account.
  None      : No total displayed.
  Anterior  : Only the total of previous transactions in the filter
              are being displayed.
  Posterior : Only the total of posterior transactions in the filter
              are being displayed.
  Both      : Both are being displayed.

@{b}Meaning of "*":@{ub} This object allows you to modify the purpose of
the "*" dialog box. If you select "Not valid", the transactions that
have not appeared by reopening the account will have a "*". If you
select "Valid" the transactions indicated in a reopened account will
have "*". PS: in this manual "*" means not valid.

@{b}Date format:@{ub} This object allows you to choose the display format
and how to determine the date. The symbols are explained as follows:
  DD   <=> Day
  MM   <=> Month
  YYYY <=> Year

@{b}Date separator:@{ub} The content of this object is used to separate the
day, month and year.

@{b}Comma position:@{ub} Allows you to choose the comma position in the
amounts. For instance, if the comma is in the third position, the
amount 12345678 will be indicated as 12345,678 .

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE IMPRESSION "Print window"

  The print window allows you to format the output by choosing a size for
each field as well as its justification.

@{b}1st column:@{ub}Indicates the name of the dialog box that is to be formatted.

@{b}2nd column:@{ub} Allows you to set up the size of the dialog box with the
number of characters.

@{b}3rd column:@{ub} Allows you to assign the value of the dialog box. "Left"
align toward left, "Right" align toward right, and "Center" align toward
the center.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE LISTES "Lists window "

  The lists window allows you to edit the possible values for the type and
the characteristics of a transaction. Thus you can create characteristics
such as miscellaneous, car etc. The window will display this list while
you are editing. The different possible actions are:

@{b}Type/Characteristics:@{ub} This "cycle" allows you to select the value list
you would like to edit.

@{b}Add:@{ub} This button adds the value contents list to the topic string.
The text cannot be empty.

@{b}Modify:@{ub} This button replaces the selected value with the one in the
topic string. The text cannot be empty.

@{b}Delete:@{ub} This button deletes the selected value.

@{b}List:@{ub} You can sort the list elements by means of drag and drop.
Select an element, hold down the mouse button, slide the pointer (up or
down) and release the mouse button: you have now successfully changed
the value order.

@{b}Topic string:@{ub} When you press Return two things might occur: If a
value is selected you will modify it otherwise you add a supplementary
value..

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE OPAUTO "Automatic operations"

  The window "Automatic operations" allows you to manage the automatic
operations. That way you can determine one periodical operation to be
repeated when necessary.

@{b}List of operations:@{ub} This list contains all of the automatic operations
which have already been set up. You can sort using drag and drop.

  @{b}New:@{ub} Allows you to initialize all the dialog boxes of the
  automatic operations.

  @{b}Delete:@{ub} Deletes selected operation.

  @{b}Add:@{ub} Adds an operation to the list.

  @{b}Modify:@{ub} Modifies the selected operation with the one you just
  determined.

@{b}Automatic operation dialog box:@{ub} Here is a description of the
automatic operation dialog box which is different from the classic
operations dialog box.

  @{b}Name:@{ub} Name of the automatic operation. Once the operation is
  added, this name will appear on the list of automatic operations.

  @{b}Period:@{ub} This dialog box indicates in numbers of months (0 to 12),
  how often an automatic operation is executed. If you select zero,
  the operation will be deleted as soon as you start it.

  @{b}Day:@{ub} This dialog box indicates the day when the operation is
  supposed to start. When the numbers shown are not applicable for
  the month (e.g.: 31. February), the highest possible number will
  be used (e.g.: 28. or 29. Febuary depending on the year).

  @{b}Transission:@{ub} It contains the date for the next launch of the
  operation. The number of the date for this day may be different
  from the one in the Day dialog box. If the number is higher than
  zero this date will be incremented daily.

  @{b}Operation:@{ub} Indicates if the dialog box for Launching Operation
  is checked. If yes, the date in this box will be identical with the
  one in the Transmission box.

  @{b}Other boxes:@{ub} Please see @{" window details " LINK DETAILS}.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE REQ "Create queries"

    The query window allows to create queries. So, you can displayed
transactions according to your criteria.

                          @{b}Queries list :@{ub}

    This list contains the queries which have been created. You can sort
the list by a drag and drop.

@{b}New :@{ub} Initialize the fields of the query.
@{b}Delete :@{ub} Delete the selected query.
@{b}Ajout :@{ub} Add the typed query to the list.
@{b}Modify :@{ub} Modify the selected query.
@{b}Name :@{ub} The "string" object which is below the list contains the
name of the query.

                        @{b} Selection criteria :@{ub}

    By default, the fields of the query allow to select all the
transactions. A "logical AND" is done, so a transaction is selected only if
all the criteria match.

@{b}Booleans :@{ub}

    Booleans are represented by "checkboxes". If the box is checked, a
transaction must have the value to be selected.

    _ Valid     : Select valid transactions.
    _ Not valid : Select not valid transactions.
    _ Credit    : Select credit transactions.
    _ Debit     : Select debit transactions.

    Example : Selection of valid and credit transactions.
        You have to check "Valid" and "Credit" boxes.

@{b}Intervals :@{ub}

    For each interval, you have to fill two "text" objects : the first for
the marked inferior, and the second for the marked superior. If the object
is empty, the marked is ignored.

    _ Transmission : Select transactions if their transmission date is
                     inside this interval.
    _ Amount       : Select transactions if their amount date is inside
                     this interval.

    Example : Selection of transaction having their transmission date
between the 10/12/96 and the 20/03/97 and their amount greater than 2000.
        You have to fill transmission interval by 10/12/1996 and
20/03/1997, and put 2000 in the first object of the amount interval and
empty the second one.

@{b}Type and characteristics :@{ub}

    "Type" and "characteristics" are two liste which respectively contain
all the types and characteristics. A transaction is selected if is type or
characteristics is above the ligne "-----------------".

    Example : Selection of transactions of type "Transfer" & "Cheque" and
of characteristics "Food".
        You have to put only "Transfer", "Cheque" and "Food" above the line
"----------" (with a drag and drop).

@{b}Character map :@{ub}

    Fields "Transmission", "Number" and "Comment" must be filled by an
AmigaDOS pattern.
    Exemple : Selection of transactions having in their comment the word
"house".
        You have to put "#?house#?" in the comment textbox.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE MENUS "Menus"

  The MUIBank menus can only be accessed from the main window (the one
  that will be displayed when you start MUIBank).

@{b}Menu Project@{ub}

  @{b}New       :@{ub} Clears all the banking operations from the memory.
  @{b}Open      :@{ub} Opens a savings account.
  @{b}Save      :@{ub} Saves the current account.
  @{b}Save As   :@{ub} Saves the current account under a different name.
  @{b}Print     :@{ub} Prints the selected operation.
  @{b}About...  :@{ub} Opens a little window displaying the author's
                 address and that MuiBank is a shareware.
  @{b}About MUI :@{ub} Opens a little window that will provide information
                 about MUI.
  @{b}Exit      :@{ub} Exit MUIBank.

@{b}Menu Preferences@{ub}

  @{b}Display :@{ub} Opens the @{" display window " LINK AFFICHAGE}.
  @{b}Print   :@{ub} Opens the @{" print window " LINK IMPRESSION}.
  @{b}Lists   :@{ub} Opens the @{" lists window " LINK LISTES}.
  @{b}Automatic operations:@{ub} Opens the @{" automatic operation window " LINK OPAUTO}.
  @{b}Query   :@{ub} Opens the @{" query window " LINK REQ}.

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE TOOLTYPES "ToolTypes"

  ToolTypes allow you to configure the applications. Currently MUIBank
has only one ToolType.

@{b}ACCOUNT:@{ub} This ToolType allows you to select the account you want
to open when you start MUIBank. For example "ACCOUNT=Example.account".

@ENDNODE

############################################################################

@NODE ENREG "Registration"

  If you like MuiBank, you should definitely register your copy with the
@{" author " LINK AUTEUR} in order to support future developments! MUIBank responds
to all needs, and definitely to small wallets!

@{b}Registration (Obligatory):@{ub}
    A registration enables you to receive the newest version of MuiBank.
  You will then be able to work your accounts without being reminded by
  a message that you should register your programm.
    A registration allows you to use five major updates of MUIBank.

                                    @{b}Price:@{ub} 55 French Francs

@{b}Postage fees (Optional):@{ub}
  If you do not have an e-mail address, you should add the shipping
  and handling costs to your bill.
                                    @{b}Price:@{ub} 15 French Francs

@{b}For users who do not live in France:@{ub}
  If you don't live in France you can pay me in your currency (please
  add 10% to the price). For the small amounts I ask you to please
  pay me in bills (no checks) and not in coins ( I cannot exchange
  coins). If you cannot help but paying me with a check, please add
  25% to the amount. The cost for shipping and handling for foreign
  countries amounts to 15 Francs FranÁais.

@{b}Remember:@{ub} @{i}A software worth using is worth buying!@{ui}

@ENDNODE

